#. type: heading *
#: modules/configuration.org:2338
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Device"
msgid "Devices"
msgstr "デバイス"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2340
msgid ""
"Peripherals that move between machines belong here, not in =hardware-"
"configuration=, which describes a host's fixed internals. Each device is a "
"switch under =my.devices.*=, exposed through the "
"=flake.modules.nixos.devices= registry; a host enables only the ones it has "
"plugged in."
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:2346
#, no-wrap
msgid "Audio"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:2348
#, no-wrap
msgid "AT2040 microphone"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2350
msgid ""
"The AT2040 is a USB microphone that also exposes a headphone output. "
"WirePlumber gives that output a higher default priority (1109) than the HDMI "
"sink (1000), so plugging the mic in silently hijacks the default output. I "
"demote the AT2040 sink to the lowest priority so the host's existing output "
"stays selected; the =media.class= guard holds back the sink alone, leaving "
"the mic input at its own high priority to still become the default source."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2357
msgid ""
"The rule matches on =alsa.card_name= rather than the serial-bearing "
"=node.name=, so it survives re-plugging and would apply to a replacement "
"unit."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2366
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  flake.modules.nixos.devices =\n"
"    {\n"
"      config,\n"
"      lib,\n"
"      ...\n"
"    }:\n"
"    let\n"
"      cfg = config.my.devices;\n"
"    in\n"
"    {\n"
"      options.my.devices.audio.at2040.enable =\n"
"        lib.mkEnableOption \"AT2040 USB mic sink demotion so it does not steal the default output\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2382
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      config = lib.mkIf cfg.audio.at2040.enable {\n"
"        services.pipewire.wireplumber.extraConfig.\"51-at2040-demote-sink\" = {\n"
"          \"monitor.alsa.rules\" = [\n"
"            {\n"
"              matches = [\n"
"                {\n"
"                  \"media.class\" = \"Audio/Sink\";\n"
"                  \"alsa.card_name\" = \"AT2040USB\";\n"
"                }\n"
"              ];\n"
"              actions.update-props = {\n"
"                \"priority.driver\" = 0;\n"
"                \"priority.session\" = 0;\n"
"              };\n"
"            }\n"
"          ];\n"
"        };\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading *
#: modules/configuration.org:2404
#, no-wrap
msgid "Browser"
msgstr "ブラウザー"

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:2406
#, no-wrap
msgid "Zen Browser"
msgstr "Zen Browser"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2408
msgid ""
"[[https://zen-browser.app/][Zen Browser]] is a Firefox-based browser with a "
"focus on privacy and customization.  Firefox derivatives were preferred over "
"Chromium-based browsers because Firefox's extension ecosystem and "
"=about:config= provide deeper control over browser behavior, and the Nix "
"ecosystem has mature tooling for managing Firefox profiles declaratively via "
"home-manager."
msgstr ""
"[[https://zen-browser.app/][Zen Browser]]はプライバシーとカスタマイズに焦点を"
"当てたFirefoxベースのブラウザです。Firefoxの拡張機能エコシステムと "
"=about:config= がブラウザの動作をより深く制御でき、NixエコシステムにはFirefox"
"のプロファイルをhome-managerで宣言的に管理する成熟したツールがあるため、"
"ChromiumベースのブラウザよりFirefox派生が選ばれました。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2413
msgid ""
"Zen Browser was chosen over vanilla Firefox for its improved UI/UX while "
"retaining full Firefox compatibility — extensions, search engines, and "
"profile settings work identically."
msgstr ""
"Zen Browserは、Firefoxの完全な互換性を保ちつつUI/UXが改善されているため、素の"
"Firefoxより選ばれました。拡張機能、検索エンジン、プロファイル設定は同じように"
"動作します。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  flake.modules.homeManager.\"zen-browser\" =\n"
"    {\n"
"      inputs,\n"
"      config,\n"
"      lib,\n"
"      pkgs,\n"
"      ...\n"
"    }:\n"
"    let\n"
"      cfg = config.my.programs.zen-browser;\n"
"    in\n"
"    {\n"
"      imports = [ inputs.zen-browser.homeModules.beta ];"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2438
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"options.my.programs.zen-browser = {\n"
"  enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"Zen Browser\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2442
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = lib.mkIf cfg.enable {\n"
"  programs.zen-browser = {\n"
"    enable = true;\n"
"    profiles.natsukium = {\n"
"      <<zen-browser-settings>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2448
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<zen-browser-search>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"            <<zen-browser-extensions>>\n"
"          };\n"
"        };\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:2458
#, no-wrap
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "設定"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2460
msgid ""
"Auto-install extensions without user prompts. By default, Firefox shows a "
"confirmation dialog for each extension installed via the profile. Setting "
"=extensions.autoDisableScopes= to 0 disables this behavior, which is "
"necessary for fully declarative extension management — otherwise the first "
"launch after a profile rebuild would require manual approval for every "
"extension."
msgstr ""
"ユーザープロンプトなしで拡張機能を自動インストールします。デフォルトでは、"
"Firefoxはプロファイル経由でインストールされる各拡張機能に確認ダイアログを表示"
"します。=extensions.autoDisableScopes= を0に設定するとこの動作が無効になり、"
"完全に宣言的な拡張機能管理に必要です。そうしないと、プロファイル再ビルド後の"
"初回起動時にすべての拡張機能について手動承認が必要になります。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:2466
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:2468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"settings = {\n"
"  \"extensions.autoDisableScopes\" = 0;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:2473
#, no-wrap
msgid "Search Engines"
msgstr "検索エンジン"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:2475
msgid ""
"Custom search engines for quick access to development-related package "
"registries and documentation. Each engine is assigned a short alias (e.g., "
"=@np=) for use in the address bar, avoiding the need to navigate to each "
"site manually."
msgstr ""
"開発関連のパッケージレジストリやドキュメントに素早くアクセスするためのカスタ"
"ム検索エンジンです。各エンジンには短いエイリアス（例: =@np=）が割り当てられて"
"おり、アドレスバーで使用でき、各サイトに手動で移動する必要がなくなります。"

